('SA-8', 'SECURITY ENGINEERING PRINCIPLES', 'SYSTEM AND SERVICES ACQUISITION', 'P1', 'MODERATE', 'The organization applies information system security engineering principles in the specification, design, development, implementation, and modification of the information system.', '800-53', 'TDB'),
('SA-9', 'EXTERNAL INFORMATION SYSTEM SERVICES', 'SYSTEM AND SERVICES ACQUISITION', 'P1', 'LOW', 'The organization:\\nRequires that providers of external information system services comply with organizational information security requirements and employ [Assignment: organization-defined security controls] in accordance with applicable federal laws, Executive Orders, directives, policies, regulations, standards, and guidance;\\nDefines and documents government oversight and user roles and responsibilities with regard  to external information system services; and\\nEmploys [Assignment: organization-defined processes, methods, and techniques] to monitor security control compliance by external service providers on an ongoing basis.\\n', '800-53', 'TDB'),
('SC-1', 'SYSTEM AND COMMUNICATIONS PROTECTION POLICY AND PROCEDURES', 'SYSTEM AND COMMUNICATIONS PROTECTION', 'P1', 'LOW', 'The organization:\\nDevelops, documents, and disseminates to [Assignment: organization-defined personnel or roles]:\\nReviews and updates the current:\\n', '800-53', 'TDB'),
('SC-10', 'NETWORK DISCONNECT', 'SYSTEM AND COMMUNICATIONS PROTECTION', 'P2', 'MODERATE', 'The information system terminates the network connection associated with a communications session at the end of the session or after [Assignment: organization-defined time period] of inactivity.', '800-53', 'TDB'),
('SC-11', 'TRUSTED PATH', 'SYSTEM AND COMMUNICATIONS PROTECTION', 'P0', NULL, 'The information system establishes a trusted communications path between the user and the following security functions of the system: [Assignment: organization-defined security functions to include at a minimum, information system authentication and re-authentication].', '800-53', 'TDB'),
('SC-12', 'CRYPTOGRAPHIC KEY ESTABLISHMENT AND MANAGEMENT', 'SYSTEM AND COMMUNICATIONS PROTECTION', 'P1', 'LOW', 'The organization establishes and manages cryptographic keys for required cryptography employed within the information system in accordance with [Assignment: organization-defined requirements for key generation, distribution, storage, access, and destruction].', '800-53', 'TDB'),
('SC-13', 'CRYPTOGRAPHIC PROTECTION', 'SYSTEM AND COMMUNICATIONS PROTECTION', 'P1', 'LOW', 'The information system implements [Assignment: organization-defined cryptographic uses and type of cryptography required for each use] in accordance with applicable federal laws, Executive Orders, directives, policies, regulations, and standards.', '800-53', 'TDB'),
('SC-14', 'PUBLIC ACCESS PROTECTIONS', 'SYSTEM AND COMMUNICATIONS PROTECTION', NULL, NULL, '[Withdrawn: Capability provided by AC-2, AC-3, AC-5, AC-6, SI-3, SI-4, SI-5, SI-7, SI-10].', '800-53', 'TDB'),
('SC-15', 'COLLABORATIVE COMPUTING DEVICES', 'SYSTEM AND COMMUNICATIONS PROTECTION', 'P1', 'LOW', 'The information system:\\nProhibits remote activation of collaborative computing devices with the following exceptions: [Assignment: organization-defined exceptions where remote activation is to be allowed]; and\\nProvides an explicit indication of use to users physically present at the devices.\\n', '800-53', 'TDB'),
('SC-16', 'TRANSMISSION OF SECURITY ATTRIBUTES', 'SYSTEM AND COMMUNICATIONS PROTECTION', 'P0', NULL, 'The information system associates [Assignment: organization-defined security attributes] with information exchanged between information systems and between system components.', '800-53', 'TDB'),
